    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The



        <emph render="bold">Slave Dealer's Record Book</emph> is a single bound volume that documents the slave-sales at Cacheu (Portuguese Guinea) from 1790-1795.  The text describes the slaves being traded, listing their price, sex, names of those selling each slave, and the name of the captain performing the shipment.  Shipments on the



        <emph render="italic">Nossa Senhore de Belton</emph> are described in much detail.</p>
    </scopecontent>
